# Digital Bricks

Extensible library of Bricks, realized as Flutter/Dart widgets  
The bricks may be connected with each other in a Kit.

Initial bricks  
\*

| Name | Purpose | Input | Output |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Backplane | Provides a technical plane for all bricks with Constant power Ground Clock | Frequency of the clock (in Hz) | Clock (true/false): Best connected by ValueNotifier\<bool\> Power: always true. Ground: always false |
| OR | Classical OR Gate with variable number of inputs | n input pins | the binary result |
| AND | Classical AND Gate with variable number of inputs | n input pins | the binary result |
| NOT | Classical binary inverter | 1 binary input | NOT input |
| XOR | Classical XOR Gate with variable number of inputs | n input pins | the binary result |
| BCD | Classical BCD (binary to decimal decoder) with variable number of input and outputs | input is binary or decimal (n digits \= 4 x n inputs | n digits \= n x 7 pin outputs |
| LED | Light emitting diode: n diodes (strip)  | n diodes if n \> 1: array of colors (start .. end color) [https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13488957/interpolate-from-one-color-to-another](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13488957/interpolate-from-one-color-to-another) binary coded single diode trigger binary coded map of value to 2^n inputs (for displaying a diode bar) | \- |
| nSegment | n segemented digit to display 7 segments: digits 0â€¦9, and some special chars: \-,.x, \<all\> \<none\> 16 segments entire ASCII  dots entire ASCII  | 7 bit decimal (each for segment) ![][image1] | \- |
| OSC | Oscillator with parameters | pulse up length pulse down length pause length 1/(up \+ down \+ pause) \= frequency | regular pulse |
